<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>215939</id>
    <title>Switching between tabs loses partially typed URL</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If you enter part of a URL in the location bar, then switch to a different tab,
then switch back to the original tab, the text you typed in the location bar is
gone.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">This is annoying, especially when trying to paste together a URL from two lines
of text, e.g.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">http://bugzilla.mozilla.org/enter_bu
    g.cgi?product=Firebird</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">I would like to paste that URL (split across lines) into the location bar
belonging to a different tab, but I can't find any way to do this.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">Every time I
switch to a different tab and back again, what I had previously typed in the bar
is lost.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">1 Start Firebird.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.3">2 C-t to open a new tab.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.4">The second tab is now displayed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.5">3 Type 'hello'.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.6">This text appears in the location bar.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.7">4 Click on the header for the first tab to switch to that tab.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.8">5 Click on the header for the second tab to switch back to the second tab.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Actual Results:  
When I switched back to the second tab, the text 'hello' I had typed was gone.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">Expected Results:  
The partially typed URL should have been preserved, ready for the user to type
or paste some more.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
